@mheon: you are right. In my tests ```\n\r``` is visually equivalent to the canonical ```\r\n``` representation. Swapping the two bytes is matter of:
```diff
       if err == nil {
-               bytes = append(bytes, '\r')
+               bytes[len(bytes)-1] = '\r'
+               bytes = append(bytes, '\n')
        }

```

I just tried this locally and it looks awesome
@marcov Thanks
LGTM
